13th Avenue, east side, from W. 24th to 25th Street, showing the Ettl Studios occupying the major part of this frontage. View 2 is limited to the structures at the N. E. corner of 24th Street. View 3 shows the westerly half of this block cleared. The freight loading platform of the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad will occupy this site in the near future.

View 3: January 25, 1930
